The course introduces seminal texts of the Estonian literary canon. It  focuses on  intertextuality, structural and comparative poetics, reception, as well as the formation of Estonian cultural identity.Objectives/eesmärkid:  An inspireing and open examination of the seminal texts of Estonian literary culture.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The students will obtain a basic understanding of the esthetically or ideologically essential role of seminal texts that have shaped our cultural identity. The theoretical points of view (intertextuality, comparative poetics, reception, etc.) and analytical skills, acquired in the lectures and seminars, form the basis for the final essay.
